An '''angiosome''' is an area of skin and underlying tissues vascularized by a source [[artery]].<ref name="Zgonis2012">{{cite book|last=Zgonis|first=Thomas|title=Surgical Reconstruction of the Diabetic Foot and Ankle|date=2 January 2012|publisher=Lippincott Williams & Wilkins|language=English |isbn=9781451153507|page=141|quote=A composite block of skin, including a specific cutaneous territory, is supplied by an artery called an angiosome.}}</ref> It is a concept that is used by [[Plastic surgery|plastic surgeons]] for the creation of [[perforator flaps]] and by [[Interventional radiology|interventional radiologists]] for the endovascular treatment of [[critical limb ischemia]].

